#X text 455 703 BIN RESOLUTION == FUNDAMENTAL FREQUENCY OF FFT = 1/N [CYCLE/SAMPLE]. IN ANALOG: (1/N) * SR \; SR = 48000 --> BIN RESOLUTION = 750 [CYCLE/SEC] \; TEST TO DO \; 1- PUT A SINGLE SAMPLE (IMPULE AT n = 10) IN \$0-INPUT \; 2- RESET \$0-NYQUIST: MEANING OSC~ FREQUENCY IS 0 -> CONSTANT 1 IN REAL AND 0 IN IMAGINARY \; 3- INVERSE-FFT ---> REPLICATE OF INPUT AT SAME PLACE (n=10). THIS IS BASICALLY A SINC FUNCTION SAMPLED AT CORRECT INTEGER PLACE \; 4- TO SEE THE SINC \, PUT SOME VALUE INSTEAD OF NYQUIST FREQUENCY (RANDOM COMPLEX SINUSOID) --> YOU WILL SEE THE SINC FUNCTION SAMPLED AT INTEGER BIN...THE SINC FUNCTION WILL BE SAMPLED SYMMETRICALLY (SO ON INTEGER BIN AT ITS TOP) WHEN COMPLEX SINUSOID MULTIPLIED IS AT INTEGER BINS --> 0 \, 750 \, 1500 \, ...[CYCLE/SEC], f 80;
#X text 453 915 BASICALLY WHAT WE ARE DOING WHEN DOING INVERSE FFT \, ABOVE AT STEP 3 \, IS TO SEE FREQUNCY DOMAIN AS TIME DOMAIN --> INVERSE-FFT IS LIKE A FFT \, BUT INPUTS ARE REAL AND IMAGINARY SPECTRUM ---> THIS PRODUCING SINC FUNCTION IN TIME-DOMAIN (JUST LIKE FT OF TIME DOMAIN PRODUCE SINC IN FREQUENCY DOMAIN) AND THIS FUNCTION IS BEING SAMPLED AT INTEGER VALUES OF N., f 81;
